This paper is about feature selection in learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG). The proposed method involves using support vector machines (SVM) with sparse regularization, which is commonly used in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. The paper also conducts experiments on datasets from Letor, which is a well-known benchmark in IR. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.DS.
